---
layout: layouts/home.njk
permalink: "/"
---

{% from 'components/labeled-link.njk' import labeledLink with context %}
{% from 'components/icon.njk' import icon %}
{% from 'components/decorative-link.njk' import decorativeLink %}

<div id="intro">
	<div id="intro-aside">
		{% image "./img/intro.jpg",
		"Photo of Alexander Sandberg",
		[null],
		"100vw" %}
	</div>

	<div id="intro-main">
		<div class="spacer-m"></div>

		{% set pageNumber = pages.home.number %}
		{% if pageNumber | isNumber %}
			<p class="suphead mono background-tertiary" aria-hidden="true">Nº {{ pageNumber | pad(2) }}</p>
			<div class="spacer-xs"></div>
		{% endif %}

		<h1 class="huge-title">Alexander Sandberg</h1>
		<div class="spacer-l"></div>

		<div class="separator-l">
			<p>I’m a self-taught, product-minded {{ icon("apple") }}
				<b>iOS/macOS Developer</b> with a background in web development and product design.</p>
			<p>When asked to describe myself with one word, I often reply with <em>curious</em>.</p>
			<div class="spacer-s"></div>
			{{ labeledLink("about", "Learn more about me →") }}
		</div>

		<div class="separator-l">
			<p>I sometimes write articles as a way to understand things better, because <em>the person who says he knows what he thinks but cannot express it usually does not know what he thinks.</em>
				<a class="subhead foreground-tertiary" href="/{{ pages.lessons.path }}228">
					<sup>(1)</sup>
				</a>
			</p>
			<div class="spacer-s"></div>
			{{ labeledLink("articles", "Read the articles →") }}

		</div>

		<div class="separator-l">
			<p>Occasionally, I also publish other random stuff that I find worth sharing with the world on my blog.</p>
			<div class="spacer-s"></div>
			{{ labeledLink("blog", "Visit the blog →") }}
		</div>

		<div class="separator-l">
			<p>I’ve always been an avid learner who loves to seek new knowledge. Over the years, I’ve collected many ”life lessons” that I want to bring along with me on this journey we call life.</p>
			<div class="spacer-s"></div>
			{{ labeledLink("lessons", "Explore the life lessons →") }}
		</div>

		<div class="separator-l">
			<p>I like to solve problems by building solutions, because <em>the best way to complain is to make things.</em>
				<a class="subhead foreground-tertiary" href="/{{ pages.lessons.path }}21">
					<sup>(2)</sup>
				</a>
			</p>
			<div class="spacer-s"></div>
			{{ labeledLink("projects", "View the projects ↓") }}
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="spacer-xxl-desktop"></div>

<aside>
	{% include "partials/social-links.njk" %}
</aside>

<div class="spacer-xxl-desktop"></div>

<p class="suphead mono background-tertiary" aria-hidden="true">Nº {{ pages.projects.number | pad(2) }}</p>
<div class="spacer-xs"></div>
<h2 id="projects" class="huge-title">Projects</h2>
{% if pages.projects.description %}
	<div class="spacer-l"></div>
	<p>{{ pages.projects.description }}</p>
{% endif %}

<div class="spacer-xxl-desktop"></div>

{% for project in projects %}
	<article class="project separator-xxl-desktop flex">
		<div class="project-main">
			<h3 class="title1">{{ project.title }}</h3>
			<span class="subhead foreground-tertiary">{{ project.subtitle }}</span>
			<div class="spacer-m"></div>
			<p>{{ project.description }}</p>
			<div class="spacer-m"></div>
			<div class="row-centered">
				<a href="{{ project.link }}">
					{{ project.link | prettyLink }}
					{% arrowForLink project.link %}
				</a>
				{{ decorativeLink(project.link, "#" + project.number | pad(3)) }}
			</div>
		</div>
		{% set image = project.image.fields %}
		{% if image %}
			<div class="project-aside">
				{% image image.file.url,
				image.title or "Preview of " + project.title + " project",
				[null],
				"100vw" %}
			</div>
		{% endif %}
	</article>
{% endfor %}